    "content": "This puzzle is very cool, but I've had some trouble understanding the details. If you feel like it, how about writing out the example step by step?\n\nSomething like:\n\nINPUT: 2 15 3 8\n\nlet's first translate the numbers from 2 to 15 into base 3:\n2 => 2\n3 => 10\n4 => 11\n5 => 12\n6 => 20\n7 => 21\n8 => 22\n9 => 100\n10 => 101\n11 => 102\n12 => 110\n13 => 111\n14 => 112\n15 => 120\n\nlet's then sort them lexicographically:\n[10, 100, 101, 102, 11, 110, 111,  112, 12, 120,  2, 20, 21, 22]\n\nthe 8th number (starting from 1!) is 112, i.e. 14 in our decimal system\nOUTPUT: 14\n\nWhat do you think?",
